`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
- The `CropComponent` being a structural superset of `CropState` (adds only `modelPath`) means `advanceCropGrowth(crop, ...)` works without any casting — TypeScript's structural typing accepts the richer type where the narrower interface is expected.
- Multiplying `dt * weatherMultiplier` (rather than adding a separate boost) keeps weather as a proportional speedup on real time, consistent with how the tree growth system feeds `weatherGrowthMult` into its rate calculation.
- Crop persistence follows the exact same delta-only pattern as trees — `recordPlantedCrop` on plant, `updateCropInDiff` on unload, `applyChunkDiff` on reload. The chunk lookup in `applyChunkDiff` uses a local `Map` built from `cropsConfig` to avoid importing across system boundaries.
`─────────────────────────────────────────────────`

